## US-001: PDF Parser Unicode Character Matching Fix

### The Problem
The PDF parser uses Chinese characters directly in regex patterns, which may not match correctly due to Unicode encoding issues when parsing PDF text content.

### The Fix

In `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts`, replace all occurrences of:
- `'节'` with `\u8282`
- `'☆'` with `\u2606`

### Changes Needed

**Find and replace these patterns:**

```typescript
// BEFORE (problematic):
const periodPattern = /(\d+)-(\d+) 节/g;
const courseMatch = text.match(/(.+?)☆/);
const regex = /第 ([\u4e00-\u9fa5]+) 周.*?(\d+)-(\d+) 节/;

// AFTER (fixed):
const periodPattern = /(\d+)-(\d+)\u8282/g;
const courseMatch = text.match(/(.+?)\u2606/);
const regex = /第 ([\u4e00-\u9fa5]+) 周.*?(\d+)-(\d+)\u8282/;
```

